Ten tubers of note cost only 10,000 Indonesian rupees (75 cents).
Over time, the economic disparity between indigenous Papuans and new migrants, who arrived in large numbers after the introduction of new flights to Nabir airport, has increased.
Few existing vacancies usually go to more educated and wealthy migrants.
Papuans rarely have the money or the skills they need to run their own competitive business.
