California, Connecticut, Delaware, Illinois, Iowa, Maine, Massachusetts, New Mexico, Oregon, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, Vermont and Washington, D.C., joined the lawsuit.
Ozone at ground level occurs when conventional pollutants from machinery, power plants, refineries and chemical plants and other sources react to the atmosphere with sunlight.
