In Russia, there will be two new territories of advanced socio-economic development - "Abaza" and "Novotroitsk."
The relevant rulings of the Russian government will come into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and economic activities of the TOR in the city of Abaza in the Republic of Hakasia have been defined.
The city, which is home to 15,000 people, will have a special legal regime of business activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investments of residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is expected that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investment to the city, as well as create more than 600 new jobs.
The list of economic activities in which the "Abaza" TOR will have a special legal regime of entrepreneurship, for example, includes crop, livestock, food, soft drinks and clothing.
Already, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the territory's dependence on the city-forming enterprise "Abakan mine."
In January 2017, the regional authorities reported that Khakasia had fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of the TOR.
The Orenburg region authorities did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk, the territory of advanced socio-economic development will also be created.
This will diversify the economy of the monocity, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise "Ural Steel" as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities in which the new TOR will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurs includes, among other things, freshwater fish farming, feed production, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first of the monocities of the Orenburg region to receive TOR status.
Recall that the territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges, which is created to attract investment and improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of the TOR are: income tax of no more than 5% for the first five years, and at least 10% over the next 5 years, social contributions of 7.6% over 10 years, the use of the free customs zone regime, preferential regime of connection to various infrastructure facilities, as well as preferential rates on rent.
